Yes, please change usages of isnan() to isfinite(). However, be careful, isnan() is true if NAN, but isfinite() is false if NAN. It is necessary to invert the sense of the test:

if (std::isnan(n)) ==> if (!std::isfinite(n))

Note the added "!" operator here. Here is a historical change for an example: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-pid-control/+/36630
